	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				If you want to know what spells rely on your charm attribute, look no further than the spell icons themselves. See the silhouette of a face? It's a charm spell. I think I read somewhere that all alteration spells are charm related as well.<BR>
<BR>
I wanted to comment that mez DOES infact wipe the hatelist. I used to think it didn't but that was back when the first offensive spell I cast was choke, which is a Damage Over Time spell.<BR>
<BR>
For those of you who have cast mez and had it immediatly fail you, it's because you have a DOT on the target and the second that DOT does any additional damage to the NPC, you're back on the hitlist.<BR>
<BR>
I use mez ALL the time to save my butt from overpulls, botched battles, and to save other people from the same thing.<BR>
<BR>
NEVER use Gate to escape a battle, the cast time on that is like 7.5 By then the MOB will be on top of you and finishing it's work. Mes is something like 2.4 if I remember correctly. That's almost three times faster!<BR>
<BR>
You can even get demonic with this spell and train something by a PC that you aren't too fond of, and then mez the MOB right by them. Casually walk away and in a few seconds the MOB wakes up and aggroes them.<BR>
<BR>
I know, it's not nice. But when you have somebody who is incessantly stealing your pulls and being a real @#$% about it, why not help them quench their thirst for battle?
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
